Peru:
Fujimori came for medical investigations into the hospital once again
The former president Alberto Fujimori was taken on Tuesday to a public hospital, in order to examine the muscle loss of his legs, his family doctor informed.
The 72 years old Fujimori who sits out 25 years of custody because of violation of the human rights during his government (1990-2000) has several illnesses, including tongue cancer which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Kongressmitglied and his personal doctor, said to the television that Fujimori would be examined for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas in order to arrest the reason for his pains and the muscle loss in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented on in his opinion Fujimori being able to be pardoned for humanitarian reasons. In spite of that he did not want this because he holds it for innocent.
It was operated four times at tongue cancer and he lost 18 kilos of weight. For this purpose further illnesses as a heavy erosive Gastritis come, the doctor counted a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, hypertension and circulation problems in the legs.
There is Fujimori since September 2007 la policía in the Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de custody institution.
In April 2009 he became 25 year of prison for the assassination of 25 persons through the death squadron of the Peruvian army, that was secretly active during his government, condemned.
